        <h2 id="whentocontact" class="govuk-heading-m">When to contact the data privacy team</h2>
        <p>Any form that is likely to involve processing of personal data should go through a <a href="https://intranet.justice.gov.uk/guidance/knowledge-information/protecting-information/privacy-reform/data-protection-impact-assessments-dpias/">data protection impact assessment (DPIA)</a> to help identify and minimise any data protection risks involved.</p>
        <p>You will need to contact your <a href="https://intranet.justice.gov.uk/guidance/knowledge-information/protecting-information/information-assurance-roles/">information assurance lead</a> or the data privacy team (<a href="mailto:privacy@justice.gov.uk">privacy@justice.gov.uk</a>) to initiate this process. Contact them as early as possible in your planning process for:</p>
        <ul>
        <li>any new form that will collect personal information from users (e.g. names, addresses, prison numbers)</li>
        <li>a change to an existing form that involves collecting new types of information or changing how it is processed</li>
        </ul>
        <p><a href="#top">Back to top</a></p>
