    <h2 id="designingtheform" class="govuk-heading-m">Designing and building your form</h2>
    <p>When designing your form, ensure that:</p>
    </ul>
    <li>you only ask for the information you need to perform your service</li>
    <li>you are clear with users why you are asking for something</li>
    <li>users can understand what you will do with their information</li>
    </ul>
    <p>To help you work out what to ask, you can carry out a <a href="https://www.uxmatters.com/mt/archives/2010/06/the-question-protocol-how-to-make-sure-every-form-field-is-necessary.php">question protocol</a>.</p>
    <p>You should also <a href="">complete the privacy notice</a> with the help of your information assurance lead or the data privacy team.</p>
    <p>Refer to the <a href="https://www.gov.uk/service-manual/design/collecting-personal-information-from-users">Service Manual guidelines on collecting personal information</a> for more guidance on designing and building your form.</p>
